+/*
+ * Custom wcwidth implementation for mosh.
+ *
+ * This replaces the system wcwidth() which is often outdated and returns
+ * -1 for valid printable Unicode characters. For example, macOS wcwidth()
+ * returns -1 for U+23F5 (BLACK MEDIUM RIGHT-POINTING TRIANGLE), causing
+ * mosh to silently drop the character.
+ *
+ * Based on Unicode 16.0 character property data.
+ *
+ * Algorithm:
+ *   - C0/C1 control characters return -1
+ *   - Characters in the zero-width table (combining marks, format
+ *     characters, Hangul jungseong/jongseong) return 0
+ *   - Characters in the wide table (East_Asian_Width W or F) return 2
+ *   - Surrogates and noncharacters return -1
+ *   - All other characters >= U+00A0 return 1
+ *
+ * Derived from Markus Kuhn's implementation, extended for Unicode 16.0.
+ */
